.packages = c("hexbin","WVPlots","hextri")
.inst <- .packages %in% installed.packages()
if(length(.packages[!.inst]) > 0) install.packages(.packages[!.inst])
lapply(.packages, require, character.only=TRUE)

functions

mixdata <-
    data.frame(x = c(rnorm(5000),rnorm(5000,4,1.5)),
               y = c(rnorm(5000),rnorm(5000,2,3)),
               a = gl(2, 5000))
hexbinplot(y ~ x, mixdata, aspect = 1,
           trans = sqrt, inv = function(x) x^2)

library(hexbin)
library(RColorBrewer)
 
# Create data
x <- rnorm(mean=1.5, 5000)
y <- rnorm(mean=1.6, 5000)
 
# Make the plot
bin<-hexbin(x, y, xbins=40)
my_colors=colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(11,'Spectral')))
plot(bin, main="" , colramp=my_colors , legend=F )

WVPlots package

if(requireNamespace("hexbin", quietly = TRUE)) {
   set.seed(634267)
   dframe = data.frame(x = rnorm(1000), y = rnorm(1000))
   print(HexBinPlot(dframe, "x", "y", "Example hexbin"))

   diamonds = ggplot2::diamonds
   print(HexBinPlot(diamonds, "carat", "price", "Diamonds example"))

   # change the colorscale
    print(HexBinPlot(diamonds, "carat", "price", "Diamonds example",
                     lightcolor="#fed98e",
                     darkcolor="#993404"))
}

hextri package

xx<-rnorm(1000)
yy<-rnorm(1000)
cc<-cut(xx*yy,c(-Inf,-.4,0,.4,Inf))

plot(xx,yy,col=(1:4)[cc])

hextri(xx,yy,cc,1:4,nbins=20,border=TRUE,style="size")
